column1: % fuel aridity metrics calculated from gridMET (Abatzoglou
% Z and Z_NOACC refer to standardized fuel aridity indices calculated across forested regions only using the primary gridded datasets of Abatzoglou (2013) and PRISM
% ZH and ZH_NOACC refer to the percent of forested land with fuel aridity exceeding 1 sigma
% FWSL and FWSL_NOACC refer to the fire weather season length expressed as a percent of normal from 1981-2010 NOACC baseline
% HFD and HFD_NOACC refer to the number of days per year with fire danger indices exceedin the 1981-2010 95th percentile as derived from the 1981-2010 NOACC baseline
% NOACC refers to metrics calculated after excluding the anthropogenic climate signal
% NaN refers to no data for the given metric and year
